pted&quot; drives me UP THE WALL!<br>
<br>
These people absolutely do not mean they will take donations - they mean that they expect to be PAID and in platinum.  The only reason they don't say so outright is because they catch flak for charging a fee for porting (or SoWing or Breeze/clarity or whatever).<br>
<br>
If they were &quot;taking donations&quot; they would accept what was offered to them be it anything from a bat wing or a rusty dagger to one hundred platinum or an item of some small (pp) value.  <br>
<br>
Donations are (as has been stated here time and time again) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> by definition</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> voluntary</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Meaning: not required, not obligatory, not necessary to receive the service being offered.<br>
<br>
I wish the folk who continually misrepresent themselves would grow some cahones, say what they mean, take the heat, and get on with it already.    &quot;Porting for a minimum charge of xxx.  But if you want to pay more - I'll thank you for it.&quot;  <br>
